        "text_PBgayj": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<ol><li>Gartner — <em>What IT Leaders Must Do to Avoid Disappointing ERP Initiatives</em> (predicts <strong>&gt;70%</strong> of recently implemented ERP initiatives will not fully meet original goals by 2027; emphasizes stakeholder engagement). <a href=\"https://www.gartner.com/en/information-technology/insights/what-it-leaders-must-do-to-avoid-disappointing-erp-initiatives?utm_source=chatgpt.com\" target=\"_blank\">Gartner</a></li><li>Experian — <em>Easing the Data Migration Burden</em> (91% undertake migrations; <strong>85%</strong> encounter challenges that impact timelines/budgets). <a href=\"https://www.edq.com/white-papers/easing-the-data-migration-burden/?utm_source=chatgpt.com\" target=\"_blank\">Experian Data Quality</a></li><li>Pacific Data Integrators summary of Bloor surveys — 2007 vs. 2011 migration success (from <strong>16%</strong> on‑time/on‑budget in 2007 to <strong>62%</strong> in 2011). <a href=\"https://info.pacificdataintegrators.com/hubfs/PDI-page-14/58.pdf?utm_source=chatgpt.com\" target=\"_blank\">info.pacificdataintegrators.com</a></li><li>Bloor Research — <em>Data Migration White Paper</em> (governance and treating migration as a sub‑project). <a href=\"https://www.existbi.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Bloor-Data_Migration-White-Paper-1.pdf?utm_source=chatgpt.com\" target=\"_blank\">ExistBI - Uniting Business & Technology</a></li><li>Panorama Consulting Group — <em>2022 ERP Report</em> (budget adherence: <strong>32.1% slightly over</strong>, <strong>9.3% significantly over</strong>; causes of overruns). <a href=\"https://f.hubspotusercontent40.net/hubfs/4439340/The%202022%20ERP%20Report%20-%20Panorama%20Consulting%20Group.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">f.hubspotusercontent40.net</a></li><li><em>An approach to estimation of degree of customization for ERP projects…</em> (ScienceDirect) — customization as material cost/effort driver; need quantitative trade‑offs. <a href=\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0164